Andrew KOOPMAN, Appellant, v. A. E. BURNETT, District Director of Immigration, District No. 31, Appellee. No. 7179. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. June 5, 1933. Max Lewis, of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellant. Peirson M. Hall, U. S. Atty., and Clyde Thomas, Asst. U. S. Atty., both of Los An-geles, Cal., for appellee.

Before WILBUR, SAWTELLE, and GARRECHT, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon stipulation of counsel for respective parties and good cause therefor appearing, ordered appeal in this cause be dismissed; mandate forthwith.
